ing certification from organizations such as leed local wind with a portfolio of nearly  mw of wind generation under contract in illinois pennsylvania and ohio we are one of the largest providers of wind energy in the region local wind is a rec product generated from instate wind farms contracted to firstenergy solutions which makes it ideal for customers who wish to support the development of green technology in their region customized green our ownership of the output of a number of renewable energy facilities in the region allows us to structure unique renewable products – such as solar or wind power directly from our renewable facilities – to meet our customers’ individual budgetary needs and sustainability objectives questions about which of these electricity options is best for your business simply request a quote or call us at    about renewable energy credits recs firstenergy solutions customers can acquire all or a percentage of their load through the purchase of recs a rec represents the environmental benefits of renewable energy generation they provide consumers and suppliers a way to support renewable energy technologies without purchasing the actual electric generation think of renewable energy as having two parts the electricity and the “green” attributes recs represent the “green” attributes of renewable energy a single rec is equal to one megawatthour mwh or  kilowatthours kwh of electric generation thirdparty regional tracking systems monitor compliance separate each megawatthour from its green component and record those attributes as recs each rec is given a unique serial number and once sold is retired from the tracking system regional tracking systems are essential for rec trading because they verify the creation and transfer of recs   allgreen is greene energy certified and meets the environmental and consumerprotection standards set forth by the nonprofit center for resource solutions learn more at wwwgreeneorg for a complete list of the resources included in allgreen view the prospective product content label to see what customers received last year view the historic product content label last modified january   home residential solutions communities we serve faq business solutions   pay my bill energy information energy services business products request a quote schools about us leadership power generation careers contact us privacy  legal statement website terms of use mobile tools and text message disclaimer business inquiries    residential inquiries     firstenergy solutions corp firstenergy solutions corp and allegheny energy supply company llc are unregulated subsidiaries of firstenergy corp neither firstenergy solutions corp nor allegheny energy supply company llc are the same company as firstenergy corp the prices of firstenergy solutions corp and allegheny energy supply company llc are not regulated by the state public utility commissions you do not have to buy electricity from firstenergy solutions corp or allegheny energy supply company llc in order to receive the same quality regulated services from firstenergy corps regulated electric utilities  ohio edison company the cleveland electric illuminating company the toledo edison company west penn power company pennsylvania power company pennsylvania electric company metropolitan edison company jersey central power  light company monongahela power company the potomac edison company and american transmission systems incorporated historic prices back to the corporate site historic prices firstenergy corp investors  suppliers  contact us  log in   home about us generation system transmission projects company history board of directors leadership team firstenergy solutions corp speakers bureau standards of conduct and affiliate restrictions our electric companies ohio edison the illuminating company toledo edison meted penelec penn power west penn power jersey central power  light mon power potomac edison environmental our initiatives stewardship c