st public corporations in america in november  firstenergy made the decision to exit the competitive power business and become a fully regulated company during the next  months it was anticipated that some generating units would be sold and some would be shut down contents  history  ohio edison  centerior  gpu  allegheny energy  generating capacity  environmental record  little blue run  executives  notable accidents and incidents  references  external links historyedit firstenergy was formed on november   when ohio edison acquired centerior energy and its subsidiaries for  billion in stock the company was acquired with plans for a restructuring and layoffs to cut costs that same month the public utilities commission of ohio puco initiated an investigation into the reliability of firstenergys energy transmission in the context of possible plant shutdowns and prior problems with centerior in  firstenergy merged with gpu inc the owner of jersey central power  light company pennsylvania electric company penelec and metropolitan edison company meted ohio edisonedit ohio edison company formerly oec on the nyse was a publicly traded holding company that began in  from the consolidation of  electric companies by  it ended up with two utility operating companies pennsylvania power and ohio edison it continued in existence until  when its merger with centerior formed firstenergy in  the pennsylvania power company became a subsidiary of ohio edison and is now one of the ten operating utilities in  the ohio edison company merged with the ohio public service company which continued to operate under its new ohio edison name it is now one of the ten firstenergy operating companies and is the main power provider for northeastern ohio outside of cleveland itself centerioredit centerior energy corporation formerly cx on the nyse was formed in  from the merger of two old operating companies centerior was based in independence ohio and existed as a publicly traded holding company for 